    <!-- §2 -->
    <section class="section" id="s2">
      <p class="section__number">Section 2</p>
      <h2>Description of Service</h2>
      <p>Pilot is a gasoline price predictability service. The Service allows users to select a coverage plan and location, establish a budgeted per-gallon rate based on a rolling average of market gas prices, and receive reimbursements when the average retail gasoline price for their selected locale exceeds that budgeted rate during the coverage period. Pilot is not a savings guarantee, discount program, or insurance product in the traditional regulatory sense.</p>
      <p>Key service mechanics:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your budgeted rate is calculated as a simple average of gas prices over the rolling window for your selected location at the time your coverage period begins.</li>
        <li>Reimbursements are calculated based on the average retail gasoline price for your selected locale — not the price you paid at any specific gas station. When that average retail price exceeds your budgeted rate, Pilot reimburses the per-gallon difference, up to the gallon cap for your plan.</li>
        <li>Reimbursements are subject to a per-period gallon cap that varies by plan. Gallons purchased beyond the applicable cap are not covered.</li>
        <li>When the average retail price for your locale is below your budgeted rate, you simply pay less at the pump. No penalty or adjustment applies.</li>
        <li>Coverage begins one (1) week after your sign-up date for both plan types.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

