      <h2>Plans and Pricing</h2>

      <h3>5.1 Available Plans</h3>

      <div class="plan-card">
        <p class="plan-card__name">7-Day Plan</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Price: $1.49 per week</li>
          <li>Gallon cap: 10 gallons per 7-day coverage period</li>
          <li>Minimum commitment: 12 consecutive weeks</li>
          <li>Budgeted rate: rolling 7-day average gas price for your selected location</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="plan-card">
        <p class="plan-card__name">30-Day Plan</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Price: $3.99 per month</li>
          <li>Gallon cap: 40 gallons per 30-day coverage period</li>
          <li>Minimum commitment: 6 consecutive months</li>
          <li>Budgeted rate: rolling 30-day average gas price for your selected location</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>5.2 Budgeted Rate</h3>
      <p>Your budgeted rate is recalculated at the start of each new coverage period based on the applicable rolling average for your chosen location. The budgeted rate will vary period to period as market prices change. Pilot does not guarantee any specific budgeted rate or price outcome.</p>

      <h3>5.3 Gallon Cap and Receipt Requirements</h3>
      <p>Reimbursements apply only to gallons up to your plan's gallon cap per coverage period. Fuel purchased beyond the gallon cap is at market price and is not covered by Pilot.</p>
      <p>To receive reimbursements, you must submit valid receipts for fuel purchases made by you, for your own personal use. By submitting a receipt, you represent and warrant that: (a) the purchase was made by you; (b) the fuel was for your personal consumption; and (c) the receipt has not been altered or falsified in any way. Submitting receipts that are forged, altered, not purchased by you, or not for your own use may result in immediate termination of your account with no refund of any remaining commitment balance.</p>
    </section>

