      <p class="section__number">Section 7</p>
      <h2>Cancellation Policy</h2>

      <h3>7.1 Commitment Period and Cancellation</h3>
      <p>Your subscription runs for a minimum commitment period — 12 weeks for the 7-Day Plan and 6 months for the 30-Day Plan — and you will be charged through the end of that commitment period. To avoid renewal into a new commitment period, you must cancel within the following windows before your commitment ends:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>7-Day Plan: cancel at least 7 days before the end of your 12-week commitment.</li>
        <li>30-Day Plan: cancel at least 30 days before the end of your 6-month commitment.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you cancel within these windows, coverage continues through the end of your current period and your subscription will not renew. No refund is issued for the current period.</p>

      <h3>7.2 Early Cancellation</h3>
      <p>If you cancel outside the window described in Section 7.1, the remaining balance of your commitment is due at the time of cancellation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>7-Day Plan: $1.49 multiplied by the number of days remaining in your commitment, divided by 7 (for example, 25 days remaining = $1.49 × 25/7 = $5.32).</li>
        <li>30-Day Plan: $3.99 multiplied by the number of days remaining in your commitment, divided by 30 (for example, 50 days remaining = $3.99 × 50/30 = $6.65).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7.3 48-Hour Grace Period</h3>
      <p>If you cancel within 48 hours of your original sign-up, no remaining balance is owed — unless you have already submitted or received a reimbursement claim during that period.</p>

      <h3>7.4 Renewal Notifications</h3>
      <p>We will notify you before your commitment renews:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>7-Day Plan: email notification sent 14 days before renewal.</li>
        <li>30-Day Plan: email notification sent 6 weeks before renewal.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7.5 Cancellation Effective Date</h3>
      <p>Cancellations initiated by you take effect at the end of the current coverage period and will not take effect mid-period. Cancellations initiated by Pilot — including for violations of these Terms, fraudulent activity, or at Pilot's sole discretion — may take effect immediately.</p>
    </section>

